<p class="c8"><span class="c41 c42">&ldquo;...two fires to concentrate, then an earth to calcinate. &nbsp;Integrate into the previous solution, and add air to cavitate. &nbsp;Aqua Regia.&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c14">The click and klack of stone tiles echo in the cave. &nbsp;A frustrated groan is quick to join them.</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c15">&ldquo;Of </span><span class="c15 c11">course</span><span class="c12">. &nbsp;Naturally, once again, the fates play favorites.&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c41 c42">&ldquo;Says you. &nbsp;Fate is for those without a plan. &nbsp;There is no fate but what you studiously prepare for.&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c12">&ldquo;Oh, yes, I can studiously prepare for crap draws. &nbsp;Is that all, or do you have another dozen operations?&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c41 c42">&ldquo;Yeah, yeah. &nbsp;I&rsquo;m done.&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c14">The soft rustle of a leather pouch, filled with similar stone tiles. &nbsp;A desperate, pleading search. &nbsp;A defeated growl.</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c12">&ldquo;Of course. &nbsp;Of course! &nbsp;Can&rsquo;t even keep Reducing with this!&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c41 c43">&ldquo;What, seriously? &nbsp;You&rsquo;ve got that big pile, and nothing to use for fuel? I call nonsense.&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c15">&ldquo;Oh, yes, I&rsquo;m just griping as a jape. &nbsp;Hah Hah. Let me just pull my fuel from the </span><span class="c15 c11">other</span><span class="c15">&nbsp;worthless pile! &nbsp;Guess I should have </span><span class="c15 c11">planned</span><span class="c12">&nbsp;to go the whole time with my pilot sputtering, huh?&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c41 c42">&ldquo;Ignore her, Drivel. &nbsp;She drew, so it&rsquo;s your go now. &ldquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c20 c19">&ldquo;Well&hellip; Uh&hellip;&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c14">A shuffling of tiles. &nbsp;Audible indecision.</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c15">&ldquo;No, don&rsquo;t &lsquo;Ignore her&rsquo;! Offer&rsquo;s still on the table, Drivel. &nbsp;I just need the one charcoal, so I can keep reducing! I promise I can give you pretty much </span><span class="c15 c11">anything else</span><span class="c12">&nbsp;on my turn in return! Look, I don&rsquo;t even need the whole charcoal, just a fire would suffice!&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c20 c19">&ldquo;Hrm&hellip;&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c41 c43">&ldquo;Don&rsquo;t do it, Drivel. &nbsp;Remember yesterday? &nbsp;Rasper&rsquo;s nothing but a scorpion.&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c12">&ldquo;Go swallow some ink, Walter. &nbsp;That was just a coincidence. Come on, Drivel. &nbsp;Just one fire.&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c20 c19">&ldquo;...Do you think I could get some xanthum in return?&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c41 c42">&ldquo;Dammit, Drivel, she can&rsquo;t tell you that! You can&rsquo;t say what&rsquo;s in your lab!&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c19 c46">&ldquo;Hey! I didn&rsquo;t ask if she </span><span class="c19 c46 c11">had</span><span class="c19 c46">&nbsp;xanthum, just if she thought she could give me what I&rsquo;d </span><span class="c19 c46 c11">need</span><span class="c20 c19">&nbsp;to make xanthum!&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c41 c42">&ldquo;Oh, come off it! That&rsquo;s the same thing!&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c41 c43">&ldquo;No, it&rsquo;s technically different. &nbsp;I mean, otherwise, you wouldn&rsquo;t be able to ask for anything, right?&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c15">&ldquo;Right! Look, Drivel, I&rsquo;m </span><span class="c15 c11">pretty sure</span><span class="c15">&nbsp;I can get you </span><span class="c15 c11">swimming </span><span class="c15">in xanthum. &nbsp;And all I need is the </span><span class="c15 c11">one</span><span class="c12">&nbsp;fire. &nbsp;You know that&rsquo;s a good deal.&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c20 c19">&ldquo;Yeah! Yeah, okay. &nbsp;Tile to you. &nbsp;As for me&hellip; Uh&hellip; I guess two earths to mixture to Occlude, then a fire to the pilot to Reduce?&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c14">Click. &nbsp;Tick Clak. &nbsp;Hesitant placement. A slight tremble.</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c41 c43">&ldquo;Three earths, two air, add to the iosate. Water to Dilute. &nbsp;Mercury. &nbsp;Your go.&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c19">Tak, tak, tak, tak. &nbsp;Confident, certain.</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c41 c42">&ldquo;I&rsquo;ll draw.&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c14">Shuf, shuf. &nbsp;A thoughtful hum.</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c41 c42">&ldquo;Okay, go ahead.&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c15">&ldquo;Hokay, so.&rdquo; &nbsp;</span><span class="c14">A slight warble to the voice. &nbsp;Giddy anticipation.</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c15">&ldquo;First, earth and fire. &nbsp;Charcoal. &nbsp; Three earth, three water, mix, Charcoal to Pilot, Reduce. &nbsp;Leucosate.<br></span><span class="c15 c11">Then</span><span class="c12">, two more earth, two air, put to pestle, air to grind. &nbsp;Add water, air to grind. &nbsp;Two xanthum. &nbsp;One to Drivel.&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c20 c19">&ldquo;Thanks! &nbsp;Okay, I&rsquo;ll-&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c15">&ldquo;Ah ah ah! Not done yet! </span><span class="c15 c11">Then</span><span class="c15">, two fire, three air, </span><span class="c15 c11">and</span><span class="c12">&nbsp;an alembic! Put to the pilot, use the second reduce of the charcoal, Iosate!&rdquo;</span></p> 
