<p class="c8"><span class="c14">You smile. &nbsp;Ancestors help you, you can&rsquo;t help it. &nbsp;<br>Sure, they&rsquo;re wasting time, and in theory that should annoy the shit out of you, but, if you&rsquo;re being really honest with yourself&hellip; it&rsquo;s relaxing. &nbsp;Familiar. &nbsp;It reminds you of simpler times. &nbsp;</span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c19">You are </span><span class="c32 c56">Renyan</span><span class="c19">, and you are currently putting the finishing touches on your notes regarding the cave that you&rsquo;ve called&hellip; well, not exactly home, but definitely your workspace for the past several months. &nbsp;You wish that you could say they were more </span><span class="c19 c11">productive</span><span class="c19">&nbsp;months. &nbsp;The fact that you&rsquo;ve effectively burnt a whole season on figuring out a cantrip is both a point of abject frustration and also small pride. &nbsp;You&rsquo;ll grant that it&rsquo;s largely useless information&hellip; but it&rsquo;s largely useless information that </span><span class="c19 c11">no one else could figure out.</span><span class="c14">&nbsp; </span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c19">Not that you can really blame your hand-picked crew for not being able to handle it. &nbsp;You mean, you didn&rsquo;t exactly pick them for their in-depth knowledge of orison minutia. &nbsp;Your selection criteria was based a lot more on mental flexibility, open perspectives, and whether or not they bugged the shit out of you. &nbsp;They were able to do their fair share in the beginning, but when shit got real, they became little more than glorified lab assistants&hellip; which is a role they pursued without complaint, argument, or apathy. &nbsp;The fact that you had an opportunity to work with people who would actually </span><span class="c19 c11">listen</span><span class="c14">&nbsp;to you went a long way to being able to crack this puzzle&hellip; even if the puzzle itself was largely worthless.</span></p> 
