<p class="c8"><span class="c25 c19">&ldquo;Supposing there actually is anything more to discover here, do you have a method in mind to continue to keep the workers of Eparchy in the dark? &nbsp;While we&rsquo;ve managed to justify our presence here with the couple of mineral seams that Rasper was able to locate, I&rsquo;m pretty sure there&rsquo;s nothing else in the area&hellip; and I&rsquo;m reasonably confident that the Samra will figure that out sooner or later. &ldquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c1"><span class="c41 c43"></span></p> 
<p class="c8"><span class="c14">Try as you might, you just can&rsquo;t keep a smug smile from crawling onto your face. &nbsp;It&rsquo;s also nice to have people ask questions that you&rsquo;ve got an answer to.</span></p> 
<p class="c1"><span class="c14"></span></p> 
<p class="c9"><span class="c24 c19">&ldquo;Ah, the answer to that is quite simple. &nbsp;When I return to Eparchy, I plan to inform them that, while conducting our mineral surveys, we&rsquo;ve managed to find this odd cave that is filled with some kind of perverse ritual! &nbsp;The fact that we need to investigate this odd discovery to see if it&rsquo;s of any threat to Eschaton should provide more than enough justification for you to stay here.&rdquo;</span></p> 
<p class="c9 c30"><span class="c24 c19"></span></p> 
