<p class="c8"><span class="c19">It is </span><span class="c19 c11">partially </span><span class="c19">true that Drivel&rsquo;s notes and recordings are&hellip; adequate&hellip; but the real reason for choosing such an obvious underdog&hellip; is that he&rsquo;s an obvious underdog. &nbsp;<br>Bakshish, as you have learned from a long, hard life of being one, are innately competitive, ambitious, and driven&hellip; up until they get fat and complacent, anyway. &nbsp;But before then, one of the quickest ways to obtain recognition and status is by standing on the backs of your fellows&hellip; ancestors know that you put more than your share under your heel. <br>However, given the number of&hellip; ahem&hellip; </span><span class="c19 c11">clandestine truths</span><span class="c19">&nbsp;that were involved in this study, leaving it in the hands of one of the more capable of their number could almost certainly cause you problems&hellip; after all, they have the perfect leverage, ready and on hand. &nbsp;Put someone who can barely keep their head above water, however, and they&rsquo;ll spend so much time fending off the ambitions of those below them that they can scarcely </span><span class="c19 c11">think</span><span class="c14">&nbsp;about how to use that time to get one over on those above them.</span></p> 
